=== 2.8 Gradient and Gradient Descent

The *gradient* of a scalar function stem:[L(\theta)] with respect to parameters stem:[\theta] is the vector of partial derivatives:

stem:[\nabla_\theta L = \left[\frac{\partial L}{\partial \theta_1}, \frac{\partial L}{\partial \theta_2}, \ldots\right]]

It points in the direction of steepest increase of stem:[L].

*Gradient descent* moves in the opposite direction to minimise stem:[L]:

stem:[\theta \leftarrow \theta - \eta \nabla_\theta L]

where stem:[\eta > 0] is the *learning rate*.

In GPT training (Chapter 12), stem:[L] is the cross-entropy loss over a batch, and stem:[\theta] contains all model weights.
The gradient is computed via backpropagation and applied by an optimiser (Adam).

