==== Example

Let stem:[L(\theta) = (\theta - 3)^2].
The gradient is stem:[dL/d\theta = 2(\theta - 3)].

Starting from stem:[\theta = 0], learning rate stem:[\eta = 0.1]:

|===
| Step | stem:[\theta] | stem:[L] | stem:[\nabla L]

| 0 | 0.0 | 9.0 | -6.0
| 1 | 0.6 | 5.76 | -4.8
| 2 | 1.08 | 3.69 | -3.84
| 10 | ~2.58 | ~0.17 | ~-0.84
|===

After many steps, stem:[\theta] converges to 3 (the minimum).

